Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Oval handle to sharpish turn. Circular stamp with rose symbol. Clay near fine light red-brown; cream slip.
Production date: 200 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes (2015) 142.)
Curator's comments: Name Klearchos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0160.35. Drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.:55, 12).
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0745)
